The paper proposes a new task of Textual Analogy Parsing (TAP) to model higher-order meaning in text, which involves identifying shared and compared aspects between analogous facts. This task falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and can be applied to various NLP applications such as automated chart generation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a model that uses an ILP to enforce structural constraints, which suggests a focus on optimization and constraint satisfaction, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper involves data analysis and modeling, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-categories.
